BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Stanford Cancer Institute Breakthroughs in Cancer: Cold Yet Vaccin
 able? RNA Vaccines for Pancreatic Cancer
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260609T230000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260610T000000
DTSTAMP:20260615T075949Z
UID:9ab7985c82d7e05d@gid-seminars.wnprc.wisc.edu
CATEGORIES:Class/Seminar
DESCRIPTION:The Stanford Cancer Institute Breakthroughs in Cancer seminar 
 series provides a platform for eminent leaders in oncology to share their 
 insights with the Stanford community. Seminars highlight innovations acros
 s basic\, translational\, clinical\, and population cancer science. \n\nJo
 in us Tuesday\, June 9\, 4-5 p.m.\, at Munzer Auditorium\, Beckman Center\
 , or Zoom for a presentation by Vinod Balachandran\, MD\, director of the 
 Olayan Center for Cancer Vaccines at Memorial Sloan Kettering Cancer Cente
 r.\n\nDr. Balachandran is a surgeon-scientist who discovered that rare lon
 g-term pancreatic cancer survivors have immune-active tumors densely infil
 trated with T cells that recognize mutation-derived proteins found on canc
 er cells. He led the first clinical trial evaluating personalized mRNA vac
 cines for pancreatic cancer\, which demonstrated that the approach can ind
 uce robust\, durable T-cell responses and improve survival. He has receive
 d numerous honors for his pioneering work\, including the 2023 Trailblazer
  Prize for Clinician-Scientists from the Foundation for the NIH\, and was 
 named one of the most influential people in health in 2025 by Time Magazin
 e and The Washington Post.\n\nThe event is open to Stanford faculty\, trai
 nees\, students\, and staff.\n\nRegistration is encouraged.\n\nEvent URL: 
 https://events.stanford.edu/event/stanford-cancer-institute-breakthroughs-
 in-cancer-pancreatic-cancer-survivors-to-solutions\n\nSource: stanford_vir
 tual
LOCATION:Beckman Center\, Munzer Auditorium
URL:https://events.stanford.edu/event/stanford-cancer-institute-breakthrou
 ghs-in-cancer-pancreatic-cancer-survivors-to-solutions
BEGIN:VALARM
ACTION:DISPLAY
DESCRIPTION:Reminder: Stanford Cancer Institute Breakthroughs in Cancer: C
 old Yet Vaccinable? RNA Vaccines for Pancreatic Cancer
TRIGGER:-PT1H
END:VALARM
END:VEVENT
