BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Smart Snacking for a Healthy Gut\, Brain\, and Heart
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260702T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260702T200000
DTSTAMP:20260615T075949Z
UID:ea3a8c042298dd53@gid-seminars.wnprc.wisc.edu
CATEGORIES:Class/Seminar
DESCRIPTION:Healthy snacks are an important part of any nutrition plan. Th
 e right snack can help maintain steady energy levels\, support brain funct
 ion\, and keep hunger in check between meals\, keeping you focused and on 
 track with your wellness goals.\n\nJoin us for a virtual demonstration whe
 re you’ll learn how to create simple and delicious anti-inflammatory sna
 cks that not only satisfy your cravings but also nourish your gut\, brain\
 , and heart health. The class will open with a short presentation on the s
 cience behind snacks that help improve the connection between your gut mic
 robiome and your heart and brain\, and those foods that can negatively imp
 act how you think\, feel and sleep.\n\nThen\, the instructor will demonstr
 ate how to put this knowledge into action! Using whole food ingredients ri
 ch in fiber\, probiotics\, antioxidants\, and omega-3s\, she will show you
  how to prepare easy\, flavorful snacks that help reduce inflammation\, pr
 omote digestion\, and support mental clarity.\n\nAll of the snacks shared 
 in this session will be easy to prepare\, requiring just a few simple ingr
 edients. You'll leave the class with new ideas for delicious\, satisfying 
 snacks that nourish both your body and mind.\n\nRecipes with detailed inst
 ructions\, ingredients\, and equipment lists will be provided after the cl
 ass for you to recreate at home. Ingredient substitutions will be suggeste
 d to accommodate most dietary restrictions.\n\nThis class will be recorded
  and a one-week link to the recording will be shared with all registered p
 articipants. \n\nTo receive incentive points\, attend at least 80% of the 
 live session or listen to the entire recording within one week.  \n\nReque
 st disability accommodations and access info.\n\n\n\nClass details are sub
 ject to change.\n\nEvent URL: https://events.stanford.edu/event/smart-snac
 king-for-a-healthy-gut-brain-and-heart\n\nSource: stanford_virtual
LOCATION:Online
URL:https://events.stanford.edu/event/smart-snacking-for-a-healthy-gut-bra
 in-and-heart
BEGIN:VALARM
ACTION:DISPLAY
DESCRIPTION:Reminder: Smart Snacking for a Healthy Gut\, Brain\, and Heart
TRIGGER:-PT1H
END:VALARM
END:VEVENT
